content: Just landed in NYC. The skyline never fails to make my heart skip a beat. First stop: meet with my mentor to discuss career moves.
Caught up with old friends from NYU. Over coffee, pitched my AI urban planning project. They loved the idea, suggested some potential investors.
Scheduled a meeting with the quant firm. Going to pitch a strategy based on the ethical trading principles I reflected on during my travels.
The pitch went surprisingly well! They're interested but want a detailed proposal. Time to put the pen to paper... or the code to screen.
Working late nights on the AI urban planning project. It's coming along, but integrating real-time data is proving challenging.
Had a breakthrough with the data integration. The project is starting to look like something I can actually present.
Reconnected with a former classmate now working in neural interface tech. He's agreed to mentor me in understanding cognitive enhancement.
